addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We can use the union of families of relational queries to compute the set of (proper) <fr:link
type="local"
href="tfmt-000T.xml"
addr="tfmt-000T"
title="Contributor to a tree"><fr:em>contributors</fr:em></fr:link> to a given tree. This is slightly subtle, because if a bibliographic tree is transcluded, we do not want its contributors to be included.</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\def\query/contributors[x]{
 \open\query
 \union-fam-rel{
  \isect{
   \transclusion-coslice{\x}
  }{
   \compl{
    \taxon{reference}
   }
  }
 }{\edges}{\outgoing}{\rel/contributors}
}]]></fr:pre></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
